cs.CC, cs.QL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with complexity and computational models in computer science, specifically with OBDDs (Ordered Binary Decision Diagrams). cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely category as the paper presents results on comparative complexity for different variants of OBDD models. cs.QL (Quantum Physics) is also likely as the paper discusses quantum OBDDs and quantum nondeterminism. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are relevant categories as OBDDs are a data structure used in algorithm design and logic. Finally, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper presents results on widths of OBDDs, which is a measure of information content.
